Norwich and Brighton drew 3-3 in an action-packed encounter at Carrow Road, with Jonny Howson, Russell Martin and Gary Hooper netting for the Canaries, who had Bradley Johnson sent off late on. 

The visitors responded through Bruno, Kazenga LuaLua and an Adrian Colunga penalty. 

Charlton and Millwall drew 0-0 and the lunchtime Yorkshire derby between Huddersfield and Sheffield Wednesday also finished goalless, with Owls striker Stevie May going closest to breaking the deadlock with a 74th-minute shot that struck both crossbar and post.

